To access the Community you need to be visible to the Community

Make myself visible*

*Your posts are never ever visible to the Piazza Community
What does this mean?
By making yourself visible
  • Employers can see who you are and the classes you've taken; they can view any profile data and resume information you've uploaded and contact you. They can never view your Piazza posts.
  • Fellow students can see who you are and classes you've taken; they do not see your resume unless you've added yourself as a Citizen of the Community. They can never view your Piazza posts.

New Feature: Tag Instructors

Instructors can now tag fellow instructors in their posts by typing the @ symbol followed by their name, e.g. @Jane Smith. Students and instructors can now tag instructors in their posts by typing the @ symbol followed by their name, e.g. @Jane Smith. When an instructor is tagged, they receive a real-time email bypassing their email notifications.

By default, only instructors can tag fellow instructors but you can enable students to also tag instructors if you wish. You can change default settings from the Manage Class tab. Instructors will see instructor names and emails in the auto complete. If enabled for students, students will only see instructor names and not instructor emails.

You can still link to posts by typing the @ symbol followed by the post number, e.g. @12
